threads.title: [SOLVED]820-3476 get to s0 state but no cpu vcore
threads.message: I have an 820-3476, ive gotten it to get to an s0 state now but im missing cpu vcore and i have a .056 in diode mode to ground on ppvcc_s0_cpu, What are the chances my cpu is fucked

threads.title: [SOLVED]820-3476 get to s0 state but no cpu vcore
threads.message: Resistance to GND on Vcore? ALL_SYS present? History?

threads.title: [SOLVED]820-3476 get to s0 state but no cpu vcore
threads.message: 93 ohms to ground. 302mv on all sys, pickle juice was spilled on it, there is come corrosion around Q8150

threads.title: [SOLVED]820-3476 get to s0 state but no cpu vcore
threads.message: Well, ALL_SYS should of course be high. Find the missing rail....

threads.title: [SOLVED]820-3476 get to s0 state but no cpu vcore
threads.message: so i think i have have short to ground on ALL_SYS i get 116 ohm to ground on that line

threads.title: [SOLVED]820-3476 get to s0 state but no cpu vcore
threads.message: i removed both q8150, u1930, and U1950 and i still get 116 ohm to ground on ALL_SYS only thing left on that line is U5000...

threads.title: [SOLVED]820-3476 get to s0 state but no cpu vcore
threads.message: nevermind, ALL_SYS also goes to U1845 which was corroded to hell, replaced it and now were all good computer boots no issues
